Police confiscated 32 dagga plants from Piet se Bos, Lorraine on Thursday 2 March 2017 Picture: Supplied Newly recruited police stumbled across a dagga plantation while on foot patrol in Lorraine on Thursday afternoon (02/03/17). Police spokeswoman Captain Sandra Janse van Rensburg said the four police constables who are based at Walmer police station came across the 32 large dagga plants in the bush near the informal settlement Piet se Bos in Lorraine. The plants were uprooted and confiscated. No arrests have been made. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share